			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Alumina regeneration and polyaluminum chloride production ; polyaluminum chloride ; acid dissolution method ; secondary aluminum slag</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">氧化铝再生与聚氯化铝生产 ; 聚氯化铝 ; 酸溶解法 ; 二次铝渣</baseName>
			</name>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:class level="0">Unit processes</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="2">Inorganic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">The parameters such as temperature and yield of these three processes were based on experimental results. Life cycle inventory data were from the average data of aluminum industries in China and calculation based on material balance. The electricity type in this study was coal based, which is in line with the actual situation of China’s aluminum industry.      The metal aluminum in secondary aluminum dross (SAD) can be recovered until 1 wt % is left through grinding and sieving. Chlorides in the solution were recovered through concentration and crystallization. Calcium chloride was used to remove fluoride. Ammonia was absorbed by hydrochloric acid and used to produce ammonium chloride. Methane produced from aluminum carbide was used as fuel gas to obtain energy. Chloride and fluoride were dissolved in water during the pretreatment. Hydrochloric acid was then used for the deactivation of active aluminum components and the dissolution of alumina. After curing at a certain temperature and duration, poly aluminum chloride can be obtained. Because of the low content and complex composition, the remaining metal chlorides were regarded as waste and landfilled. In this scenario, the active aluminum component was also completely deactivated. The recovery rate of alumina was 95%.</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
