		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">The metal aluminum in secondary aluminum dross (SAD) can be recovered until 1 wt % is left through grinding and sieving. Chlorides in the solution were recovered through concentration and crystallization. Calcium chloride was used to remove fluoride. Ammonia was absorbed by hydrochloric acid and used to produce ammonium chloride. Methane produced from aluminum carbide was used as fuel gas to obtain energy. Chloride and fluoride were dissolved in water during the pretreatment. Hydrochloric acid was then used for the deactivation of active aluminum components and the dissolution of alumina. After curing at a certain temperature and duration, poly aluminum chloride can be obtained. Because of the low content and complex composition, the remaining metal chlorides were regarded as waste and landfilled. In this scenario, the active aluminum component was also completely deactivated. The recovery rate of alumina was 95%. </technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The described process is used in the recycling of secondary aluminum slag (SAD) to produce alumina and polyaluminum chloride (PAC). Alumina regenerated from this process can be used in applications such as aluminum metal production and as a precursor for various aluminum compounds. Polyaluminum chloride produced is commonly utilized as a coagulant in water treatment plants for potable and wastewater treatment.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">该工艺用于回收二次铝渣（SAD），生产氧化铝和聚氯化铝（PAC）。通过这一过程再生的氧化铝可用于铝金属生产等应用，以及作为各种铝化合物的前体。生产的聚氯化铝通常用作自来水和污水处理厂的絮凝剂。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="114e8f8c-47ed-471f-1c3a-d0fcc4c14dbd" uri="../sources/114e8f8c-47ed-471f-1c3a-d0fcc4c14dbd.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">DkTcb95uKoQt8Tx9Onycz23pnOg.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
