			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="en">When employing this life cycle assessment data, ensure to adhere to the cut-off rules defined by the included cutoff system model, focusing solely on the environmental impacts attributable to the SAD recovery within the aluminum life cycle, excluding transportation. Account for the coal-based electricity usage consistent with the aluminum industry's practice in China. The recovery process sequence - involving grinding, sieving, concentration, crystallization, and curing should be accurately reflected and the final landfilling of low-content complex metal chlorides should be considered as waste disposal. The alumina recovery rate of 95% needs to be incorporated into the material balance calculations.</useAdviceForDataSet>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="zh">使用此生命周期评估数据时，请确保根据所包含的截止系统模型遵守截止规则，仅关注铝生命周期内与SAD回收相关的环境影响，不包括运输。考虑与中国铝工业实践一致的煤电使用。回收过程序列—包括磨碎、筛分、浓缩、结晶和固化应准确反映，最后将含量低的复杂金属氯化物视为废物处理应考虑在内。需要将95%的氧化铝回收率纳入材料平衡计算。</useAdviceForDataSet>
		</dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativeness>
		<completeness>
			<common:other xml:lang="en">1) Cut-off rules; 2) The system boundaries were set by applying a cutoff system model based on cradle-to-grave thinking, which only focused on the impacts of SAD recovery in the entire life cycle of aluminum, including raw material production and waste disposal; 3) transportation was not included.</common:other>
			<common:other xml:lang="zh">1) 截止规则；2) 系统边界是通过应用基于 &quot;从摇篮到坟墓 &quot;思维的截止系统模型来设定的，该模型只关注 SAD 回收在铝的整个生命周期中的影响，包括原材料生产和废物处置；3) 不包括运输。</common:other>
		</completeness>
